{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872594291,"sessionID":"ses_285c109fcffefKkioxaLLN9YuV","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3f004b001Utpr7AoCvNhy2X","messageID":"msg_d7a3ef6f6001kxLpcF7CImTCEQ","sessionID":"ses_285c109fcffefKkioxaLLN9YuV","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_dc0d52ca57dd4e90be32a4b2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure - look at the root directory and key subdirectories\n2. Any existing spec files (delta-spec.md, spec.md, or similar) - search for them\n3. Any existing manifests/ directory or YAML configuration files related to RBAC (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n4. Any existing OpenSpec format examples in the project\n5. The project's conventions for specs and manifests\n\nSearch broadly:\n- Look at the root directory structure\n- Find any *.md files that look like specs\n- Find any YAML files in manifests/ directories\n- Search for RBAC-related content (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding, ClusterRole)\n- Look for any OpenSpec or spec format examples\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project structure overview\n- Existing spec files and their format\n- Existing RBAC manifests if any\n- Any conventions or patterns used in the project","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_285c0ebcfffeKTCPMLHKXa971J (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the AgentCube project. Here is the complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive AgentCube Project Analysis\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\n```\nagentcube/                          (repository root)\n├── cmd/                            # Go binaries (entry points)\n│   ├── agentd/                     # Idle cleanup controller\n│   ├── cli/                        # Python CLI (kubectl-agentcube)\n│   ├── picod/                      # PicoD daemon (sandbox code execution)\n│   ├── router/                     # Session-aware HTTP router\n│   └── workloadmanager/            # Main control plane API server\n├── pkg/                            # Go packages\n│   ├── agentd/                     # Idle cleanup logic\n│   ├── apis/                       # CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n│   ├── common/                     # Shared utilities\n│   ├── picod/                      # PicoD daemon logic\n│   ├── router/                     # Router logic\n│   ├── store/                      # Redis/Valkey session store\n│   └── workloadmanager/            # Workload manager controllers\n├── manifests/                      # Kubernetes/Helm manifests\n│   └── charts/\n│       └── base/                   # Helm chart (apiVersion v1, version 0.1.0)\n│           ├── Chart.yaml\n│           ├── values.yaml\n│           ├── crds/               # CRD definitions\n│           │   ├── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n│           │   └── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n│           └── templates/\n│               ├── _helpers.tpl\n│               ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n│               ├── agentcube-router.yaml\n│               ├── rbac-router.yaml\n│               ├── rbac/\n│               │   └── workloadmanager.yaml\n│               └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml\n├── changes/                        # Change requests (AR-001 through AR-031)\n│   └── AR-XXX/                     # Each change has proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, optionally delta-spec.md\n├── sdk-python/                     # Python SDK (agentcube package)\n├── python-sdk/                     # Python SDK spec.md\n├── cli-toolkit/                    # CLI toolkit spec.md\n├── deployment/                     # Deployment spec.md\n├── sandbox-orchestration/          # Sandbox orchestration spec.md\n├── session-routing/                # Session routing spec.md\n├── session-store/                  # Session store spec.md\n├── idle-cleanup/                   # Idle cleanup spec.md\n├── ci-cd/                          # CI/CD spec.md\n├── code-execution/                 # Code execution spec.md\n├── integrations/                   # Integrations spec.md (Dify plugin, PCAP analyzer)\n├── delta-spec.md                   # Root-level delta spec (AR-029: SDK HTTP client)\n├── project.md                      # OpenSpec Project Context\n├── design.md                       # AR-029 design document\n├── proposal.md                     # AR-028 proposal document\n├── tasks.md                        # AR-023 tasks document\n├── test_spec.md                    # TDD test case specification\n├── go.mod / go.sum                 # Go module (github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube)\n└── .sdd_prompt.md                  # Prompt configuration\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Existing Spec Files and Their Format\n\nThe project uses an **OpenSpec** format with two tiers of specs:\n\n#### A. Base Specs (`spec.md`) -- Found in feature subdirectories\n\nThese are comprehensive, foundational specifications for major subsystems. Locations:\n\n| File | Subject |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/spec.md` | Helm chart, deployments, RBAC, CRDs, Docker images, Makefile |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` | CRD schemas, HTTP API, auth, sandbox lifecycle, garbage collection |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md` | CLI commands (pack, build, publish, invoke, status) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/spec.md` | Dify plugin, PCAP analyzer |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/spec.md` | Python SDK |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-store/spec.md` | Session store |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-routing/spec.md` | Session routing |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md` | Idle cleanup |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/spec.md` | CI/CD |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/spec.md` | Code execution |\n\n**Base spec format:**\n```markdown\n# <Feature> Specification\n\n## Purpose\n<One-paragraph description>\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: <Requirement name>\nThe system SHALL <requirement statement>.\n\n#### Scenario: <scenario name>\n- **GIVEN** <precondition>\n- **WHEN** <action>\n- **THEN** <expected outcome>\n```\n\n#### B. Delta Specs (`delta-spec.md`) -- Found in `changes/AR-XXX/` directories\n\nThese are incremental specifications tied to specific change requests (AR = AgentCube Request). There are **23 delta-spec.md files** across AR-002 through AR-031 (not every AR has one; AR-001, AR-008, AR-009, AR-012-AR-016 are missing delta-spec.md).\n\n**Delta spec format:**\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX: <Title> -- Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n- **Module:** `<module-name>`\n- **Language:** <Language>\n- **Size:** <S|M|L>\n- **Base specs:** `<path/to/base/spec.md>`, ...\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: <Requirement name>\nThe system SHALL <requirement statement>.\n\n#### Scenario: <scenario name>\n- **GIVEN** <precondition>\n- **WHEN** <action>\n- **THEN** <expected outcome>\n\n## File Changes\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n```\n\n#### C. Root-level delta-spec.md\n\nThe file at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` is AR-029 (SDK HTTP client layer) -- a fully populated 366-line spec covering HTTP session factory, ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient, connection pooling, utility functions, and exception hierarchy.\n\n#### D. AR-031 delta-spec.md (RBAC) -- Currently a Skeleton\n\nThe file at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md` is currently a **stub/placeholder** with TODO comments:\n```markdown\n# AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n- **Module:** `manifests`\n- **Language:** YAML\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** <!-- TODO: reference base specs -->\n\n## Delta Requirements\n<!-- TODO: Define requirements with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios -->\n\n## File Changes\n<!-- TODO: List file changes as a table: Action | File | Description -->\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing RBAC Manifests\n\nThe project has **three RBAC-related YAML files** in the Helm chart:\n\n#### A. WorkloadManager RBAC (always rendered)\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n\n- **ServiceAccount:** `workloadmanager` (namespace-scoped)\n- **ClusterRole:** `workloadmanager` with rules for:\n  - `agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes` (full CRUD)\n  - `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxclaims`, `sandboxtemplates`, `sandboxwarmpools`, `sandboxwarmpools/status`\n  - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters`, `codeinterpreters/status`, `codeinterpreters/finalizers`\n  - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes`, `agentruntimes/status`\n  - Core: `pods`, `secrets`\n  - Auth: `authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews`\n- **ClusterRoleBinding:** `workloadmanager` binding SA to ClusterRole\n\n#### B. Router RBAC (conditionally rendered)\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n\n- Guarded by `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}` (default: `false`)\n- **ServiceAccount:** `agentcube-router` (or custom name from `router.serviceAccountName`)\n- **Role:** namespace-scoped, grants full verbs on `secrets`\n- **RoleBinding:** binds SA to Role\n\n#### C. Volcano Scheduler RBAC (conditionally rendered, mixed with non-RBAC resources)\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n\n- Guarded by `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}` (default: `false`)\n- **ServiceAccount:** `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n- **ClusterRole:** `volcano-agent-scheduler` with extensive rules (CRDs, pods, nodes, storage, scheduling, leases, resource claims, etc.)\n- **ClusterRoleBinding:** `volcano-agent-scheduler-role`\n- Also contains: ConfigMap, Service, Deployment (mixed in same file)\n\n---\n\n### 4. OpenSpec Format Conventions\n\nThe project follows a well-defined OpenSpec methodology:\n\n#### Document Types per Change Request (AR-XXX)\n\n| File | Purpose | Status |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| `proposal.md` | Purpose, scope (in/out), architecture summary, impact analysis, alternatives, dependencies, status checkboxes | Always present |\n| `design.md` | Architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy, implementation steps | Always present |\n| `delta-spec.md` | Incremental requirements in GIVEN/WHEN/THEN format, file change table | Present in 23 of 31 ARs |\n| `tasks.md` | Checkbox tasks with dependency graph, parallelizable groups, acceptance criteria | Always present |\n\n#### Spec Format Conventions\n\n1. **Normative language:** SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n2. **Requirement blocks:** `### Requirement: <name>` followed by `The system SHALL ...`\n3. **Scenario blocks:** GIVEN/WHEN/THEN format (BDD-style)\n4. **File change tables:** `| Action | File | Description |`\n5. **Context header:** Module, Language, Size, Base specs references\n6. **Base specs** live in feature directories (`deployment/spec.md`, `sandbox-orchestration/spec.md`, etc.)\n7. **Delta specs** live in `changes/AR-XXX/delta-spec.md` and reference base specs\n\n---\n\n### 5. Key Conventions and Patterns\n\n#### Helm Chart Conventions\n- Chart name: `agentcube`, API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version: `v1alpha1`\n- All namespaced resources use `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n- RBAC resources are in `templates/rbac/` subdirectory (partial -- router RBAC is still at `templates/rbac-router.yaml`)\n- `_helpers.tpl` provides `agentcube.name`, `agentcube.fullname`, `agentcube.chart`, `agentcube.labels`, `agentcube.selectorLabels`\n- Values control: `router.rbac.create` (default `false`), `volcano.scheduler.enabled` (default `false`)\n\n#### RBAC Naming Conventions (current, per AR-031 proposal)\n- ServiceAccount: `<component>` or `agentcube-<component>`\n- ClusterRole/Role: Currently `<component>` (AR-031 proposes adding `agentcube-` prefix)\n- ClusterRoleBinding/RoleBinding: Currently `<component>` (AR-031 proposes `-binding` suffix)\n- Labels: `app: <component>` (AR-031 proposes adding `app.kubernetes.io/*` labels)\n\n#### AR-031 (RBAC Refactoring) -- Current State\n- **proposal.md:** Fully written -- proposes consolidating all RBAC into `templates/rbac/`, adding `values.yaml` switches, standardizing naming with `agentcube-` prefix, and adding Kubernetes standard labels\n- **design.md:** Skeleton with TODO placeholders\n- **delta-spec.md:** Skeleton with TODO placeholders\n- **tasks.md:** Skeleton with TODO placeholders\n\n---\n\n### 6. Summary of All Spec Files Found\n\n| Path | Type | Status |\n|------|------|--------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` | Delta spec (AR-029) | Fully populated (366 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/test_spec.md` | TDD test spec | Populated (29 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md` | Project context | Populated (45 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/spec.md` | Base spec | Fully populated (96 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` | Base spec | Fully populated (176 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md` | Base spec | Fully populated (197 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/spec.md` | Base spec | Fully populated (191 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md` | Delta spec | Fully populated (402 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md` | Delta spec | **Skeleton/TODO** (16 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-031/proposal.md` | Proposal | Fully populated (116 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-031/design.md` | Design | **Skeleton/TODO** (51 lines) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md` | Tasks | **Skeleton/TODO** (25 lines) |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_285c0ebcfffeKTCPMLHKXa971J","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project","time":{"start":1775872447534,"end":1775872594288}}}}
