{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775872619688,"sessionID":"ses_285c109fcffefKkioxaLLN9YuV","part":{"id":"prt_d7a41b49b001mjx2iOCkLkf16G","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a418fa6001CMOniseX7WAIMV","sessionID":"ses_285c109fcffefKkioxaLLN9YuV","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":36138,"input":36013,"output":99,"reasoning":26,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.010145963}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775872621390,"sessionID":"ses_285c109fcffefKkioxaLLN9YuV","part":{"id":"prt_d7a41bb4a001g3u343NMylkw7J","messageID":"msg_d7a41b4bd001EnsQxxMc6gYJmg","sessionID":"ses_285c109fcffefKkioxaLLN9YuV","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872722101,"sessionID":"ses_285c109fcffefKkioxaLLN9YuV","part":{"id":"prt_d7a41de38001XVNWaCrmXSBQZc","messageID":"msg_d7a41b4bd001EnsQxxMc6gYJmg","sessionID":"ses_285c109fcffefKkioxaLLN9YuV","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_12956d3351554b689742a076","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `manifests`\n- **Language:** YAML\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `deployment/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: RBAC directory consolidation\n\nAll RBAC resources SHALL be defined under `templates/rbac/` directory. The file `rbac-router.yaml` SHALL be moved to `templates/rbac/router.yaml`. The Volcano scheduler RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) SHALL be extracted from `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` into `templates/rbac/volcano-scheduler.yaml`. The original `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` SHALL retain only non-RBAC resources (ConfigMap, Service, Deployment).\n\n#### Scenario: RBAC files are in the correct directory\n- **GIVEN** the chart directory `manifests/charts/base/templates/`\n- **WHEN** the directory listing is inspected\n- **THEN** `rbac/` contains `workloadmanager.yaml`, `router.yaml`, and `volcano-scheduler.yaml`\n- **AND** `rbac-router.yaml` no longer exists at the templates root\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano template retains only non-RBAC resources\n- **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n- **WHEN** `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` is rendered\n- **THEN** the output contains ConfigMap, Service, and Deployment for the Volcano scheduler\n- **AND** no ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, or ClusterRoleBinding appears from this template\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano RBAC renders from the new location\n- **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n- **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is run\n- **THEN** the output contains ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, and ClusterRoleBinding for the Volcano scheduler from `rbac/volcano-scheduler.yaml`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: WorkloadManager RBAC values gate\n\nA new `values.yaml` key `workloadmanager.rbac.create` SHALL control whether WorkloadManager RBAC resources are rendered. The default SHALL be `true` to maintain backward compatibility. The template `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` SHALL be wrapped in a conditional `{{- if .Values.workloadmanager.rbac.create }}`.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager RBAC enabled by default\n- **GIVEN** default `values.yaml` (no explicit `workloadmanager.rbac.create` set)\n- **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is run\n- **THEN** the output contains ServiceAccount `workloadmanager`, ClusterRole `workloadmanager`, and ClusterRoleBinding `workloadmanager`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager RBAC explicitly disabled\n- **GIVEN** `--set workloadmanager.rbac.create=false`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** no WorkloadManager ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, or ClusterRoleBinding appears in the output\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager RBAC explicitly enabled\n- **GIVEN** `--set workloadmanager.rbac.create=true`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the output contains all three WorkloadManager RBAC resources\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Volcano scheduler RBAC values gate\n\nA new `values.yaml` key `volcano.scheduler.rbac.create` SHALL control whether Volcano scheduler RBAC resources are rendered. When the value is empty string `\"\"` (default), it SHALL follow `volcano.scheduler.enabled`. When set explicitly to `true` or `false`, it SHALL override the enabled flag. The template `rbac/volcano-scheduler.yaml` SHALL use the conditional logic: `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.rbac.create | default .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`.\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano RBAC follows enabled by default\n- **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` and `volcano.scheduler.rbac.create` unset (empty)\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** no Volcano scheduler RBAC resources appear\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano RBAC follows enabled when true\n- **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true` and `volcano.scheduler.rbac.create` unset\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the output contains Volcano scheduler ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, and ClusterRoleBinding\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano RBAC explicitly disabled regardless of enabled\n- **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true --set volcano.scheduler.rbac.create=false`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** no Volcano scheduler RBAC resources appear in the output\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano RBAC explicitly enabled regardless of disabled\n- **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=false --set volcano.scheduler.rbac.create=true`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the output contains Volcano scheduler ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, and ClusterRoleBinding\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Router RBAC gate unchanged\n\nThe existing `router.rbac.create` gate (default `false`) SHALL remain unchanged in behavior. The Router RBAC template moved to `templates/rbac/router.yaml` SHALL preserve the same conditional rendering logic.\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC off by default after move\n- **GIVEN** default values after the file move\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** no Router ServiceAccount, Role, or RoleBinding appears\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC enabled after move\n- **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the output contains Router ServiceAccount, Role, and RoleBinding with the same names and rules as before the move\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: ClusterRole naming with agentcube- prefix\n\nAll ClusterRole resources SHALL be named with the `agentcube-` prefix to avoid cluster-wide naming conflicts. The naming convention SHALL be `agentcube-<component>`. This applies to WorkloadManager and Volcano scheduler ClusterRoles.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole has agentcube- prefix\n- **GIVEN** default values\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the WorkloadManager ClusterRole is named `agentcube-workloadmanager`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano ClusterRole has agentcube- prefix\n- **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the Volcano scheduler ClusterRole is named `agentcube-volcano-agent-scheduler`\n\n#### Scenario: ClusterRoleBinding references the prefixed ClusterRole name\n- **GIVEN** default values\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** `ClusterRoleBinding/agentcube-workloadmanager-binding` has `roleRef.name: agentcube-workloadmanager`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: ClusterRoleBinding/RoleBinding naming with -binding suffix\n\nAll ClusterRoleBinding and RoleBinding resources SHALL be named with the `-binding` suffix. The naming convention SHALL be `agentcube-<component>-binding`. This applies to WorkloadManager, Router, and Volcano scheduler bindings.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager binding has -binding suffix\n- **GIVEN** default values\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding is named `agentcube-workloadmanager-binding`\n\n#### Scenario: Router binding has -binding suffix\n- **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the Router RoleBinding is named `agentcube-router-binding`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano binding has -binding suffix\n- **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the Volcano scheduler ClusterRoleBinding is named `agentcube-volcano-agent-scheduler-binding`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: ServiceAccount naming consistency\n\nServiceAccount names SHALL remain consistent with their corresponding Deployment names. WorkloadManager SA stays as `workloadmanager`. Router SA stays as `agentcube-router` (or custom `router.serviceAccountName`). Volcano scheduler SA stays as `volcano-agent-scheduler`.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager SA name unchanged\n- **GIVEN** default values\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the ServiceAccount is named `workloadmanager`\n\n#### Scenario: Router SA respects serviceAccountName value\n- **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=my-router-sa`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the Router ServiceAccount is named `my-router-sa`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano SA name unchanged\n- **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the Volcano scheduler ServiceAccount is named `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: RBAC permissions unchanged\n\nNo apiGroups, resources, or verbs SHALL be added, removed, or modified from any existing RBAC rule. The permission scope of WorkloadManager, Router, and Volcano scheduler roles SHALL be identical before and after this change (only names and file locations change).\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager ClusterRole rules preserved\n- **GIVEN** default values\n- **WHEN** the rendered ClusterRole `agentcube-workloadmanager` is inspected\n- **THEN** it contains the exact same rules as the original `ClusterRole/workloadmanager`:\n  - `agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes` with full CRUD\n  - `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxclaims`, `sandboxtemplates`, `sandboxwarmpools` with full CRUD\n  - `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxwarmpools/status` with `get,update,patch`\n  - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters` with full CRUD\n  - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters/status` with `get,update,patch`\n  - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters/finalizers` with `update`\n  - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes` with `get,list,watch`\n  - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes/status` with `update,patch`\n  - core `pods` with `get,list,watch`\n  - core `secrets` with full CRUD\n  - `authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews` with `create`\n\n#### Scenario: Router Role rules preserved\n- **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true`\n- **WHEN** the rendered Role is inspected\n- **THEN** it grants `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` on `secrets` in the release namespace (unchanged)\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano ClusterRole rules preserved\n- **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n- **WHEN** the rendered ClusterRole `agentcube-volcano-agent-scheduler` is inspected\n- **THEN** it contains the exact same rules as the original `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` (CRDs, pods, nodes, storage, scheduling, leases, resourceclaims, nodeshards, etc.)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Kubernetes standard labels on RBAC resources\n\nAll RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, Role, ClusterRoleBinding, RoleBinding) SHALL include the labels `app.kubernetes.io/name`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance`, and `app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac`. The `app.kubernetes.io/name` value SHALL match the component name (e.g., `workloadmanager`, `router`, `volcano-scheduler`). These labels SHALL be applied via the `agentcube.labels` helper combined with the component-specific label.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager RBAC has kubernetes standard labels\n- **GIVEN** default values and release name `my-release`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the WorkloadManager ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, and ClusterRoleBinding each have labels:\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/instance: my-release`\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac`\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC has kubernetes standard labels\n- **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true` and release name `my-release`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the Router ServiceAccount, Role, and RoleBinding each have labels:\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/name: router`\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/instance: my-release`\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano RBAC has kubernetes standard labels\n- **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true` and release name `my-release`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** the Volcano scheduler ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, and ClusterRoleBinding each have labels:\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/name: volcano-scheduler`\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/instance: my-release`\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/component: rbac`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: _helpers.tpl RBAC name helpers\n\nThe `_helpers.tpl` file SHALL define two new template helpers:\n- `agentcube.rbacName` — returns `agentcube-<component>` for ClusterRole/Role naming\n- `agentcube.rbacBindingName` — returns `agentcube-<component>-binding` for ClusterRoleBinding/RoleBinding naming\n\nBoth helpers SHALL accept a component name as a parameter and truncate to 63 characters with trailing `-` trimmed.\n\n#### Scenario: rbacName helper generates prefixed name\n- **GIVEN** the helper `agentcube.rbacName` is called with component `workloadmanager`\n- **WHEN** the template is rendered\n- **THEN** it returns `agentcube-workloadmanager`\n\n#### Scenario: rbacBindingName helper generates binding name\n- **GIVEN** the helper `agentcube.rbacBindingName` is called with component `workloadmanager`\n- **WHEN** the template is rendered\n- **THEN** it returns `agentcube-workloadmanager-binding`\n\n#### Scenario: Long component names are truncated\n- **GIVEN** the helper `agentcube.rbacName` is called with a component name that would exceed 63 characters when prefixed\n- **WHEN** the template is rendered\n- **THEN** the result is truncated to 63 characters with trailing `-` trimmed\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: values.yaml RBAC key tree\n\nThe `values.yaml` SHALL include the following RBAC-related keys:\n- `workloadmanager.rbac.create: true` (new, default true)\n- `router.rbac.create: false` (existing, unchanged)\n- `volcano.scheduler.rbac.create: \"\"` (new, empty string to follow `enabled`)\n\nComments SHALL document the purpose of each key and the default behavior.\n\n#### Scenario: values.yaml parses with new RBAC keys\n- **GIVEN** the file `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n- **WHEN** it is parsed as YAML\n- **THEN** `workloadmanager.rbac.create` exists and equals `true`\n- **AND** `router.rbac.create` exists and equals `false`\n- **AND** `volcano.scheduler.rbac.create` exists and equals `\"\"` (empty string)\n\n#### Scenario: RBAC key comments document behavior\n- **GIVEN** `values.yaml` is read as text\n- **WHEN** the `volcano.scheduler.rbac.create` key area is inspected\n- **THEN** a comment explains that empty string means the value follows `volcano.scheduler.enabled`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Helm upgrade backward compatibility\n\nAn existing AgentCube release installed before this change SHALL upgrade without resource deletion or recreation of RBAC objects that would cause downtime. Helm's native resource tracking (by GVK + namespace + name) SHALL handle the file move and rename correctly.\n\n#### Scenario: Upgrade from pre-AR-031 release\n- **GIVEN** a release installed with the chart before RBAC consolidation (ClusterRole named `workloadmanager`, ClusterRoleBinding named `workloadmanager`)\n- **WHEN** `helm upgrade` is run with the post-AR-031 chart\n- **THEN** the old ClusterRole `workloadmanager` is deleted and new ClusterRole `agentcube-workloadmanager` is created\n- **AND** the old ClusterRoleBinding `workloadmanager` is deleted and new ClusterRoleBinding `agentcube-workloadmanager-binding` is created\n- **AND** no WorkloadManager pods are restarted during the upgrade (only RBAC resources change)\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC file move is transparent\n- **GIVEN** a release with `router.rbac.create: true` installed before the file move\n- **WHEN** `helm upgrade` is run with the post-AR-031 chart\n- **THEN** Router RBAC resources are tracked by their GVK + name, not by template filename\n- **AND** no Router RBAC resources are deleted and recreated\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: RBAC resource binding integrity\n\nEach ClusterRoleBinding/RoleBinding SHALL correctly reference its corresponding ClusterRole/Role and ServiceAccount after the naming changes. The `roleRef` in bindings SHALL use the new prefixed ClusterRole/Role name, and `subjects` SHALL reference the correct ServiceAccount in the release namespace.\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager binding integrity\n- **GIVEN** default values and release namespace `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** `ClusterRoleBinding/agentcube-workloadmanager-binding` has:\n  - `roleRef.kind: ClusterRole`, `roleRef.name: agentcube-workloadmanager`\n  - `subjects[0].kind: ServiceAccount`, `subjects[0].name: workloadmanager`, `subjects[0].namespace: agentcube`\n\n#### Scenario: Router binding integrity\n- **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` and release namespace `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** `RoleBinding/agentcube-router-binding` has:\n  - `roleRef.kind: Role`, `roleRef.name: agentcube-router`\n  - `subjects[0].kind: ServiceAccount`, `subjects[0].name: agentcube-router`, `subjects[0].namespace: agentcube`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano binding integrity\n- **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true` and release namespace `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** templates are rendered\n- **THEN** `ClusterRoleBinding/agentcube-volcano-agent-scheduler-binding` has:\n  - `roleRef.kind: ClusterRole`, `roleRef.name: agentcube-volcano-agent-scheduler`\n  - `subjects[0].kind: ServiceAccount`, `subjects[0].name: volcano-agent-scheduler`, `subjects[0].namespace: agentcube`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Helm lint passes on RBAC templates\n\nAll RBAC templates SHALL pass `helm lint` without errors or warnings related to RBAC resource definitions.\n\n#### Scenario: Lint passes with default values\n- **GIVEN** the chart at `manifests/charts/base`\n- **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is run\n- **THEN** no errors are reported\n- **AND** no warnings related to RBAC resources are reported\n\n#### Scenario: Lint passes with all RBAC enabled\n- **GIVEN** the chart at `manifests/charts/base`\n- **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base --set router.rbac.create=true --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true` is run\n- **THEN** no errors are reported\n- **AND** no warnings related to RBAC resources are reported\n\n---\n\n## File Changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| Modify | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Add `workloadmanager.rbac.create: true` and `volcano.scheduler.rbac.create: \"\"` keys |\n| Modify | `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Add `agentcube.rbacName` and `agentcube.rbacBindingName` template helpers |\n| Modify | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Add `{{- if .Values.workloadmanager.rbac.create }}` gate; rename ClusterRole to `agentcube-workloadmanager`; rename ClusterRoleBinding to `agentcube-workloadmanager-binding`; add `app.kubernetes.io/*` labels |\n| Rename | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` → `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/router.yaml` | Move into rbac/ directory; rename Role to `agentcube-router`; rename RoleBinding to `agentcube-router-binding`; add `app.kubernetes.io/*` labels |\n| Create | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/volcano-scheduler.yaml` | Extract ServiceAccount/ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding from volcano template; rename ClusterRole to `agentcube-volcano-agent-scheduler`; rename ClusterRoleBinding to `agentcube-volcano-agent-scheduler-binding`; add `volcano.scheduler.rbac.create` gate; add `app.kubernetes.io/*` labels |\n| Modify | `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Remove ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding; retain ConfigMap, Service, Deployment only |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20